General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) A prospective developer who submits an application for a proposed
2 brownfields agreement for review by the Department shall pay an initial fee
3 of two thousand dollars ($2,000).
4 (2) A prospective developer who enters into a brownfields agreement with the
5 Department shall pay pay, on a schedule that the Department may specify, a
6 fee in an amount equal to the full cost to the Department and the Department
7 of Justice of all activities related to the brownfields agreement, including but
8 not limited to negotiation of the brownfields agreement, public notice and
9 community involvement, and monitoring the implementation of and
10 compliance with the brownfields agreement. agreement and requirements of
11 this Part regarding the Notice of Brownfields Property. The procedure by
12 which the amount of this fee is determined shall be established by agreement
13 between the prospective developer and the Department and shall be set out as
14 a part of the brownfields agreement. The fee imposed by this subdivision shall
15 be paid in two installments. The first installment shall be due at the time the
16 prospective developer and the Department enter into the brownfields
17 agreement and shall equal all costs that have been incurred by the Department
18 and the Department of Justice at that time less the amount of the initial fee
19 paid pursuant to subdivision (1) of this subsection. The Department shall not
20 enter into the brownfields agreement unless the first installment is paid in full
21 when due. The second installment shall be due at the time the prospective
22 developer submits a final report certifying completion of remediation under
23 the brownfields agreement and shall include any additional costs that have
24 been incurred by the Department and the Department of Justice, including all
25 costs of monitoring the implementation of the brownfields agreement.
26 (3) Any prospective developer or owner of properties subject to a recorded Notice
27 of Brownfields Property who is out of compliance with the requirements of
28 this Part regarding the Notice shall pay a fee to the Department and the
29 Department of Justice sufficient to cover the costs to the State to enforce or
30 otherwise seek to correct the noncompliance.
31 (b) Fees and interest imposed under this section shall be credited to the Brownfields
32 Property Reuse Act Implementation Account.
33 (c) If a prospective developer fails to pay the full amount of any fee due under this
34 section, interest on the unpaid portion of the fee shall accrue from the time the fee is due until
35 paid at the rate established by the Secretary of Revenue pursuant to G.S. 105-241.21. A lien for
36 the amount of the unpaid fee plus interest shall attach to the real and personal property of the
37 prospective developer and to the brownfields property until the fee and interest is paid. The
38 Department may collect unpaid fees and interest in any manner that a unit of local government
39 may collect delinquent taxes."
40 SECTION 4.(b) G.S. 105-277.13 reads as rewritten:
41 "§ 105-277.13. Taxation of improvements on brownfields.
42 (a) Qualifying improvements on brownfields properties are designated a special class of
43 property under Article V, Sec. 2(2) of the North Carolina Constitution and shall be appraised,
