21 SOLID WASTE BENEFICIAL REUSE CLARIFICATION
22 SECTION 5.(a) G.S. 130A-309.05 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 130A-309.05. Regulated wastes; certain exclusions.
24 (a) Certain Wastes Regulated as Nonhazardous. – Notwithstanding other provisions of
25 this Article, the following waste shall be regulated pursuant to this Part:
26 (1) Medical waste; and
27 (2) Ash generated by a solid waste management facility from the burning of solid
28 waste.
29 (b) Management of Ash Generated from Burning of Solid Waste. – Ash generated by a
30 solid waste management facility from the burning of solid waste shall be disposed of in a properly
31 designed solid waste disposal area that complies with standards developed by the Department for
32 the disposal of the ash. The Department shall work with solid waste management facilities that
33 burn solid waste to identify and develop methods for recycling and reusing incinerator ash or
34 treated ash.
35 (c) Recovered Material. – Recovered material is not subject to regulation as permitting
36 requirements for solid waste under this Article. In order for a material that would otherwise be
37 regulated as solid waste to qualify as a recovered material, the The Department may require any
38 person who owns or has control over the material to demonstrate that the material meets the
39 requirements of this subsection. In order to protect public health and the environment, the
40 Commission subsection or may require the person to obtain a beneficial use determination from
41 the Department in accordance with subsection (d) of this section. The Department may adopt
42 rules to implement this subsection. Materials that are accumulated speculatively, as that term is
43 defined under 40 Code of Federal Regulations § 261 (July 1, 2014 Edition), shall not qualify as
44 a recovered material, and shall be subject to regulation as solid waste. In order to qualify as a
45 recovered material, the material. The material shall be managed as a valuable commodity in a
46 manner consistent with the desired use or end use, and all of the following conditions shall be
47 met:
48 (1) Seventy-five percent (75%), by weight or volume, of the recovered material
49 stored at a facility at the beginning of a calendar year commencing January 1,
50 shall be removed from the facility through sale, use, or reuse by December 31
51 of the same year.
